08,"answer_count":1,"title":"What kind of larvae are these?","body":"<p>My uncle was helping us spray the garage for ants, and he stumbled across a huge batch of some type of larvae. According to him...<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>\"It looked like a long, narrow clump of mud. When I broke it open, all of these larvae fell out. Whatever bugs were inside scattered pretty quickly!\"<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Geography:<\/strong> We're in Los Angeles, CA (southwestern USA)<\/li>\n<li><strong>Season:<\/strong> It's late summer here (early September)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p><strong>Exhibit A:<\/strong> The pile of larvae...<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/mOOti.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/mOOti.jpg\" alt=\"larvae\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p><strong>Exhibit B:<\/strong> A similar husk of \"mud\" found in our garage. When it was shattered, nothing fell out...<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/GceGE.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/GceGE.jpg\" alt=\"similar empty husk\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>My uncle thinks it's termites... I'm certainly hoping it isn't. <\/p>\n","question_id":37498,"tags":["entomology","species-identification"],"score":4,"accepted_answer_id":38578,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":226,"up_vote_count":4,"last_edit_date":1441329322},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e86681e49622d52817b36fd2a4c936b7?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":8014,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8014/martin-thoma","reputation":441,"display_name":"Martin Thoma","accept_rate":83},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e86681e49622d52817b36fd2a4c936b7?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":8014,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8014/martin-thoma","reputation":441,"display_name":"Martin Thoma","accept_rate":83},"score":1,"post_id":38545,"edited":false,"creation_date"